<subSubSection id="C3115DA56E7C4078FF485EAF17CA9C07" pageId="17" pageNumber="278" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB40E2E6E7C4078FF485EAF17CA9C07" blockId="17.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="17" pageNumber="278">
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7C4078FF485EAF16979DDE" authorityName=": Mayer" authorityYear="1974" box="[199,410,693,716]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="278" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrops">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7C4078FF485EAF16979DDE" box="[199,410,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="278">Epigonus macrops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described based on two 
<typeStatus id="54B0B08C6E7C4078FCE15EAF14DD9DDF" box="[878,976,693,717]" pageId="17" pageNumber="278">syntypes</typeStatus>
from the eastern Indian Ocean (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A73DF6E7C4078FAC15EAE17DE9DE2" pageId="17" pageNumber="278" refId="ref17837" refString="Brauer, A. (1906) Die Tiefsee-Fische. I. Systematischer Teil. In: Chun, C. (Ed.), Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Deutschen Tiefsee-Expedition &quot; Valdivia &quot;, 1898 - 99. Vol. 15. Gustav Fischer, Jena, 432 pp., 18 pls." type="book chapter">Brauer 1906</bibRefCitation>
). Although we did examine the larger specimen of these, deposited in the 
<collectionCode id="ED1A96EB6E7C4078FB9D5EC2135C9DFD" box="[1042,1105,728,751]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum f�r Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="17" pageNumber="278">ZMB</collectionCode>
, a smaller specimen has been lost.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3115DA56E7C4078FF485F3A12449CDA" pageId="17" pageNumber="278" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BB40E2E6E7C4078FF485F3A12449CDA" blockId="17.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="17" pageNumber="278">
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7C4078FF485F3A15BE9C2A" authority="McCosker &amp; Long, 1997" authorityName="McCosker &amp; Long" authorityYear="1997" box="[199,691,799,824]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="278" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="merleni">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7C4078FF485F3A16839C2A" box="[199,398,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="278">Epigonus merleni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A73DF6E7C4078FE195F0515BE9C2A" box="[406,691,799,824]" pageId="17" pageNumber="278" refId="ref20198" refString="McCosker, J. E. &amp; Long, D. J. (1997) A new species of the deepwater cardinalfish Epigonus (Perciformes: Epigonidae) from the Galapagos Islands. Ichthyological Research, 44, 125 - 129. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 02678691" type="journal article">McCosker &amp; Long, 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described on the basis a single specimen collected from the Galápagos Islands. It was considered to be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7C4078FC425F5F13409C4E" authorityName=": Mayer" authorityYear="1974" box="[973,1101,837,860]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="278" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrops">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7C4078FC425F5F13409C4E" box="[973,1101,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="278">E. macrops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having 11 + 14 Vertebrae and 57 lateral-line scales, but first author’s examination of 
<typeStatus id="54B0B08C6E7C4078FCA35F7D14839C92" box="[812,910,871,896]" pageId="17" pageNumber="278">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7C4078FC3B5F7313259C92" authorityName="McCosker &amp; Long" authorityYear="1997" box="[948,1064,872,896]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="278" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="merleni">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7C4078FC3B5F7313259C92" box="[948,1064,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="278">E. merleni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed that it actually has 10 + 15 vertebrae, 48 + 5 lateral-line scales, and a luminescent window near the pelvic-fin base (see Okamoto 
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7C4078FAEE5F9712999CB6" box="[1377,1428,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="278">et al</emphasis>
. 2012). Therefore, they concluded that 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7C4078FDCA5FAB15B49CDA" authorityName="McCosker &amp; Long" authorityYear="1997" box="[581,697,944,968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="278" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="merleni">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7C4078FDCA5FAB15B49CDA" box="[581,697,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="278">E. merleni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E7C4078FC4C5FAB12489CDA" authority="(Okamoto et al. 2012)" authorityName="Okamoto et al." authorityYear="2012" box="[963,1349,943,968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="278" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrops">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7C4078FC4C5FAB134F9CDA" box="[963,1090,945,968]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="278">E. macrops</emphasis>
(Okamoto 
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E7C4078FB4E5FAB13FE9CDA" box="[1217,1267,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="278">et al</emphasis>
. 2012)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
